Overview

This is a simple Python-based tool for converting video files to audio files. It utilizes popular libraries such as MoviePy and FFMpeg to extract the audio content from a video file and save it in a desired audio format (e.g., MP3).
Features

    Video to Audio Conversion: Convert various video formats (e.g., MP4, MKV) to audio files.
    Audio Format Options: Save the extracted audio in different formats, such as MP3, WAV, etc.
    Easy-to-Use: A straightforward command-line interface for quick and simple conversions.
    Dependencies: Requires MoviePy and FFMpeg. You can install them using the provided requirements.txt file.

Prerequisites

    Python 3.x installed
    Pip (Python package installer) installed

Installation

    Clone this repository to your local machine:

    bash

git clone https://github.com/your_username/video-to-audio-converter.git

Change into the project directory:

bash

cd video-to-audio-converter

Install the required dependencies:

bash

    pip install -r requirements.txt

Usage

Run the script from the command line with the following syntax:

bash

python video_to_audio.py -i input_video.mp4 -o output_audio.mp3

Options:

    -i or --input: Path to the input video file.
    -o or --output: Path to save the output audio file.
    -f or --format: Output audio format (e.g., mp3, wav).

Example

bash

python video_to_audio.py -i input_video.mp4 -o output_audio.mp3 -f mp3

This command will convert the "input_video.mp4" to an MP3 audio file named "output_audio.mp3".
